{"version":3,"term":{"cols":108,"rows":30},"timestamp":1784818246,"command":"./run-demo.sh","env":{"SHELL":"/bin/zsh"}}
[0.096, "o", "\u001b[1;36m  agentstack — import once, use it across every coding CLI\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;35m▎ Today: two CLIs, two formats, two half-setups. Claude Code knows 'github':\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.510, "o", "\u001b[2m$ cat ~/.claude.json\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.533, "o", "  {\r\n    \"mcpServers\": {\r\n      \"github\": {\r\n        \"command\": \"/usr/bin/env\",\r\n        \"args\": [\"npx\", \"-y\", \"github-mcp\"],\r\n        \"env\": { \"GITHUB_TOKEN\": \"ghp-demo-FAKE-not-a-real-secret-0000\" }\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ Codex knows 'tldraw' — in TOML, at a different path:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.513, "o", "\u001b[2m$ cat ~/.codex/config.toml\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.534, "o", "  [mcp_servers.tldraw]\r\n  command = \"/usr/bin/env\"\r\n  args = [\"npx\", \"-y\", \"tldraw-mcp\"]\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[2mNeither CLI has the other's server, and a live token sits in plain JSON.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ Import everything once — one command, one manifest:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.519, "o", "\u001b[2m$ agentstack init --yes --secrets env\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.570, "o", "  🔍  Found 2 coding tool(s) and their native configs:\r\n        Claude Code   ~/.claude.json\r\n        Codex CLI     ~/.codex/config.toml\r\n  📥  Importing 2 MCP server(s) from those configs:\r\n        github   runs /usr/bin/env npx -y github-mcp\r\n        tldraw   runs /usr/bin/env npx -y tldraw-mcp\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[2m🔐\u001b[0m  \u001b[1m\u001b[33mFound 1 plaintext token(s) in your live CLI configs\u001b[39m\u001b[0m — lifted to secure references:\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "        \u001b[32m${GITHUB_TOKEN}\u001b[39m   \u001b[2mserver 'github' (env GITHUB_TOKEN)\u001b[0m\r\n        \u001b[2mThe manifest stays commit-safe; real values resolve locally at apply time.\u001b[0m\r\n  📦  Files agentstack will manage:\r\n        .agentstack/agentstack.toml   the manifest — written by this import\r\n        .mcp.json                     Claude Code · MCP servers (this project)\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "        .codex/config.toml            Codex CLI · MCP servers (this project)\r\n        Native files are written by the next `agentstack apply --write`, not now.\r\n"]
[0.037, "o", "  \u001b[2m🔑\u001b[0m  Stored 1 token(s) in .env (gitignored)\r\n  \u001b[2m✅\u001b[0m  Wrote /private/tmp/agentstack-demo.f90wHY/project/.agentstack/agentstack.toml\r\n  \r\n  Import complete.\r\n    Manifest:  /private/tmp/agentstack-demo.f90wHY/project/.agentstack/agentstack.toml   (the source of truth your CLIs render from)\r\n    From:      Claude Code · Codex CLI\r\n    Imported:  2 MCP server(s)\r\n    Undo:      agentstack restore --last --write\r\n    Next:      agentstack apply --write   (render this setup into your CLIs)\r\n               agentstack doctor          (check the result)\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ The manifest is the portable source of truth — and it is commit-safe:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.515, "o", "\u001b[2m$ grep -n GITHUB_TOKEN .agentstack/agentstack.toml\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.523, "o", "  13:GITHUB_TOKEN = \"${GITHUB_TOKEN}\"\r\n"]
[0.018, "o", "  \u001b[32mPASS\u001b[0m the manifest holds ${GITHUB_TOKEN}, never the value (it lives in the gitignored .env)\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;35m▎ Render the one manifest back into BOTH native formats:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.507, "o", "\u001b[2m$ agentstack apply --scope global --write\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.604, "o", "    \u001b[32m+ GITHUB_TOKEN = \"${GITHUB_TOKEN}\"\u001b[39m\r\n    \u001b[32m✓\u001b[39m wrote 2 server(s)\r\n  \r\n  Applied to 2 target(s).\r\n  \u001b[36m→\u001b[39m Restart or reopen your agent CLI(s) so they pick up the new config.\r\n    \u001b[2mundo: agentstack restore\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ Now each CLI has BOTH servers, in its own format:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.518, "o", "\u001b[2m$ cat ~/.claude.json ~/.codex/config.toml\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.522, "o", "  {\r\n    \"mcpServers\": {\r\n      \"github\": {\r\n        \"type\": \"stdio\",\r\n        \"command\": \"/usr/bin/env\",\r\n        \"args\": [\r\n          \"npx\",\r\n          \"-y\",\r\n          \"github-mcp\"\r\n        ],\r\n        \"env\": {\r\n          \"GITHUB_TOKEN\": \"ghp-demo-FAKE-not-a-real-secret-0000\"\r\n        }\r\n      },\r\n      \"tldraw\": {\r\n        \"type\": \"stdio\",\r\n        \"command\": \"/usr/bin/env\",\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "        \"args\": [\r\n          \"npx\",\r\n          \"-y\",\r\n          \"tldraw-mcp\"\r\n        ]\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.006, "o", "  [mcp_servers.tldraw]\r\n  command = \"/usr/bin/env\"\r\n  args = [\"npx\", \"-y\", \"tldraw-mcp\"]\r\n  \r\n  [mcp_servers.github]\r\n  command = \"/usr/bin/env\"\r\n  args = [\"npx\", \"-y\", \"github-mcp\"]\r\n  \r\n  [mcp_servers.github.env]\r\n  GITHUB_TOKEN = \"ghp-demo-FAKE-not-a-real-secret-0000\"\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1mAsserting the outcome:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.007, "o", "  \u001b[32mPASS\u001b[0m Claude Code gained 'tldraw' (imported from Codex)\r\n"]
[0.006, "o", "  \u001b[32mPASS\u001b[0m Codex gained 'github' (imported from Claude Code)\r\n"]
[0.012, "o", "  \u001b[32mPASS\u001b[0m the token resolved into the native config; the manifest still holds the placeholder\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ Is everything healthy? One status command:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.508, "o", "\u001b[2m$ agentstack doctor\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.584, "o", "    \u001b[32m✓\u001b[39m no library-backed profile skills to verify\r\n  \u001b[2m·\u001b[0m 6 section(s) for features this project doesn't use are hidden — \u001b[1magentstack doctor --all\u001b[0m shows everything.\r\n  \r\n  0 error(s), 0 warning(s).\r\n"]
[0.009, "o", "  \u001b[32mPASS\u001b[0m doctor is clean (0 errors, 0 warnings)\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ Changed your mind? Every write is recorded — undo the render, then the import:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.508, "o", "\u001b[2m$ agentstack restore --last --write   # undoes the apply\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.566, "o", "    \u001b[36m↩\u001b[39m Codex CLI · servers          revert /tmp/agentstack-demo.f90wHY/home/.codex/config.toml\r\n  \u001b[32m✓\u001b[39m undone — reverted files show up as pending again; re-run `agentstack apply` to re-render.\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[2m$ agentstack restore --last --write   # undoes the import\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.542, "o", "    \u001b[31m✗\u001b[39m manifest · import            delete /private/tmp/agentstack-demo.f90wHY/project/.agentstack/agentstack.toml\r\n  \u001b[32m✓\u001b[39m undone — reverted files show up as pending again; re-run `agentstack apply` to re-render.\r\n"]
[0.008, "o", "  \u001b[32mPASS\u001b[0m ~/.claude.json is byte-identical to where it started\r\n"]
[0.006, "o", "  \u001b[32mPASS\u001b[0m ~/.codex/config.toml is byte-identical to where it started\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "  \u001b[32mPASS\u001b[0m the manifest and the secrets .env are gone — the machine is exactly as it was\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ Import once → both CLIs in sync → clean doctor → fully reversible.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.507, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1mSummary:\u001b[0m 8 passed, 0 failed\r\n"]
[0.013, "x", "0"]
